# AI-Pandit Cursor Rules

# Project: Vedic Astrology BTR Engine — Turborepo monorepo
# apps/web = Next.js 15 | apps/api = Express.js | packages/db = Drizzle | packages/shared = Types

# TypeScript
- Use strict mode. No `any` types.
- Explicit return types on exported functions.
- Early returns over deep nesting.
- Zod schemas for all input validation.

# Error Handling
- Use AppError hierarchy (ValidationError, NotFoundError, AIServiceError).
- Never throw raw Error(). Include context object.

# Backend
- Logger: Pino only. Never console.log.
- Structured logs: logger.info({ sessionId }, 'message').
- API responses: sendSuccess(), sendError(), sendPaginated().
- Auth: Clerk middleware on all protected routes.

# Frontend
- State: Zustand for global state. React Server Components for data.
- Styling: TailwindCSS. No inline styles.
- Animation: Framer Motion.
- No prop drilling beyond 2 levels.

# Security
- AES-256-GCM encryption for birth data.
- Support both 3-part and 4-part encryption formats.
- XSS sanitization on all user inputs.
- Never commit .env files.

# Critical files (understand before modifying):
# - apps/api/src/lib/seconds-precision-btr.ts (6-stage BTR pipeline)
# - apps/api/src/lib/queue-manager.ts (job queue, max 3 concurrent)
# - apps/api/src/lib/vedic-astrology-engine.ts (Vedic calculations)
# - apps/web/app/rectify/[id]/page.tsx (main analysis page)

# See CLAUDE.md for full documentation.
